The paper deals with trajectory planning for an autonomous vehicle on a race track, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm presented involves optimization and control, which are also relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of optimization techniques and the iterative nature of the algorithm suggest that it could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision for track boundary detection, which could also place it under computer vision (cs.CV).
